Workshop ""ON""","- The opponent can ask for you to switch visual or sound cosmetics at any time and you must do it going into the next game. (If requested within the first 5 seconds of game startup, the game will just be restarted)

- Winner must alert loser of character-switching

- DSR, A player cannot return to any stage they have previously won on without the consent of their opponent 

-Although not required, we highly recommend connecting with an Ethernet cable. We'll try our best to be understanding with Wi-Fi, but players will be disqualified if their connection makes matches unplayable.

- Workshop Characters in the roster allowed ONLY

- Stages are chosen in game one using a 1-1-1-1 striking format (with the higher seed striking first), the winner of each game bans 3 stages, not counting those affected by DSR described in Section E.",,"Any bugs/glitches that happen will be handled with the same stock reset of the situation (Also goes for desyncs)

